{
    "id": "dictionaryutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "DictionaryUtil",
    "description": "Store values by a key instead of a position — like player name → score. Add, look up, check, remove, and loop through key/value pairs.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/dictionaryutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "dictionaryutil",
        "dictionary",
        "key",
        "value",
        "map"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "ListUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/listutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "ColliderUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/colliderutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "DictionaryUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A **dictionary** stores values you look up by a **key** instead of a position. Think of a real dictionary: you look up a word (the key) to find its meaning (the value). In a game you might map each player's name to their score, or each item ID to how many the player owns."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Use a dictionary (instead of a [list](/docs/uniscript/en-us/listutil)) when each value has a natural name to find it by, and order doesn't matter."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Creating one and adding pairs"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Map each player's name to their score.",
                "Dictionary scores = DictionaryUtil.New();",
                "",
                "DictionaryUtil.Add(scores, \"Alice\", 100);",
                "DictionaryUtil.Add(scores, \"Bob\", 75);",
                "",
                "// Look Alice's score back up by her name.",
                "int aliceScore = DictionaryUtil.Get(scores, \"Alice\");   // 100"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`New()`", "Creates a new empty dictionary."],
                ["`New(size)`", "Creates a dictionary prepared to hold `size` pairs."],
                ["`Add(dict, key, value)`", "Adds a new key with its value."],
                ["`Set(dict, key, value)`", "Sets a key's value — adds it if new, replaces it if it already exists."],
                ["`Get(dict, key)`", "Looks up the value stored under a key."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "important",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Each key can appear only **once**. Use `Add` for a brand-new key; use `Set` when you want to add-or-update safely (for example, raising a score that may already exist)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Checking and removing"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`ContainsKey(dict, key)`", "`true` if that key exists. Check this before `Get` to avoid missing keys."],
                ["`ContainsValue(dict, value)`", "`true` if some key holds that value."],
                ["`Remove(dict, key)`", "Removes a key and its value."],
                ["`Count(dict)`", "How many pairs are stored."],
                ["`Clear(dict)`", "Removes everything."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "if (DictionaryUtil.ContainsKey(scores, \"Alice\"))",
                "{",
                "    int s = DictionaryUtil.Get(scores, \"Alice\");",
                "    DictionaryUtil.Set(scores, \"Alice\", s + 10);   // give Alice +10",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Looking at everything inside"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`Keys` gives you a [list](/docs/uniscript/en-us/listutil) of every key, which you can loop through. `ForEach` is the quickest way to visit every pair — it runs your method once per pair, handing it the `key` and the `value`."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Print every player and their score.",
                "DictionaryUtil.ForEach(scores, this, \"PrintScore\", null);",
                "",
                "void PrintScore(object key, object value, object extra)",
                "{",
                "    Debug.Log(key + \" has \" + value + \" points\");",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Dictionary`", "`New`", "—"],
                ["`Dictionary`", "`New`", "`int size`"],
                ["`void`", "`Add`", "`Dictionary dictionary, object key, object value`"],
                ["`bool`", "`Remove`", "`Dictionary dictionary, object key`"],
                ["`bool`", "`ContainsKey`", "`Dictionary dictionary, object key`"],
                ["`bool`", "`ContainsValue`", "`Dictionary dictionary, object value`"],
                ["`int`", "`Count`", "`Dictionary dictionary`"],
                ["`void`", "`Clear`", "`Dictionary dictionary`"],
                ["`object`", "`Get`", "`Dictionary dictionary, object key`"],
                ["`void`", "`Set`", "`Dictionary dictionary, object key, object value`"],
                ["`List`", "`Keys`", "`Dictionary dictionary`"],
                ["`void`", "`ForEach`", "`Dictionary dictionary, uniscript, string callMethod, object value`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "To list every value, loop the keys from `Keys` and `Get` each one — or just use `ForEach`, which already hands you both the key and value for every pair."
        }
    ]
}
